questions.question_text:
Under standard conditions, complete combustion of 0.050 mol of propane  \( \left(\mathrm{C}_{3}\mathrm{H}_{8}\right) \)  gives 111 kJ of heat. Which of the following is the standard enthalpy change of formation of propane?

(Standard enthalpy change of formation of  \( \mathrm{H}_{2}\mathrm{O}(\mathrm{l})=-286\ \mathrm{kJ}\ \mathrm{mol}^{-1} \) ;
standard enthalpy change of formation of  \( \mathrm{CO}_{2}(\mathrm{~g})=-394\ \mathrm{kJ}\ \mathrm{mol}^{-1} \) )
